d moron couldn't look at their health regen and see they are not getting the sitting bonus and tell me this?! If you do not get the sitting health regen on a horse then you won't get the sitting innate mana regen that you do get at certain levels. So now I am left to assume the med while casting part of the horses was a damn lie too. Can someone please tell me the absolute truth about which regen you do and do not get on a horse, I am so damn sick of the boobs I have been talking to for information all this time...<br>
<br>
        Liveye (lvl 64 Wizard Ayonae Ro)<br>
<br>
PS- Sorry for harshness of this post but I cannot stand people who tell me things they know &quot;for sure&quot; and they really didn't look closely at all and therefore I am left with false information. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphyr>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/03 5:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Urgent question on horses/drogmors, please help.</span><hr size=1> You don't get HP regen as you noticed.<br>
You do get Mana regen. Unless you are moving or have attack turned on.<br>
<br>
If you feel like testing it yourself, just click off all mana regen buffs and your horse. Watch how slow your mana goes up while standing. Summon the horse. Notice the massive increase in mana recovery. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44185">Vending Machine, Disciple of Zomm, and husband to Sarrena Destini</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
