I stand against the chaos and the cross of holy fire&quot; - N. Peart</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=codegurux>CodeguruX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 238<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/03 5:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Urgent question on horses/drogmors, please help.</span><hr size=1> I know I get the standing meditation ability and I guess the med while casting is true since it seems to be going up at the same rate while I cast the 15 second barrier of force. What I'm worried about is do we get the innate sitting mana regen that has nothing to do with meditation such as the point we get at level 65. I my self can time my nukes to get every single med pulse and I don't see a reason to sit on a horse if all it means is I lose the few points of innate sitting mana regen we get and i get a med pulse or 2 the 1 or 2 times I'll cast BoF in an hour.<br>
<br>
                   Liveye (lvl 64 Wizard Ayonae Ro) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solarax6975>solarax6975</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 442<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/03 5:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Urgent question on horses/drogmors, please help.</span><hr size=1> medding is the act of getting more than sitting mana regen.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=codegurux>CodeguruX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/03 5:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Urgent question on horses/drogmors, please help.</span><hr size=1> Medding is a skill level ability, just like FT adds standing mana regen we get points of sitting mana regen at certain levels. I don't want to give up 2 or 3 points of certain sitting mana regen just to sit on a horse. Just asking if anyone knows for sure wether we do or do not get the sitting (non mediation) mana regen while on a horse. If someone knows FOR SURE please tell me...<br>
<br>
                          Liveye (lvl 64 Wizard Ayonae Ro) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=colossusa>Colossusa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Grimstaff's Arch Nemesis</span><br>  Posts: 894<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/03 6:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Urgent question on horses/drogmors, please help.</span><hr size=1> FOR SURE?  That's a bit strange sounding as there has been like 500 threads about it.<br>
<br>
I would assume that 500 threads stating mana regen and 0 threads about HP regen means it is real.<br>
<br>
Yes you get Mana regen.  Whoever told you get HP regen never owned a horse.<br>
