<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Sorcerer and dancing legend<br>
Owner of Binky the Wonder Horse</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1315<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 6:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Urgent question on horses/drogmors, please help.</span><hr size=1> Whether you miss out on the 2 pts or not (I dunno) you gain far more than you lose because of the med ticks during casting.<br>
<br>
If instead of sitting on a horse medding you clicked it off and sat on the ground, when you stood to cast a spell (or cast the horse) you'd lose med time. Let alone the times you cant sit immediately cos of sit aggro.<br>
<br>
Believe me, I've fought with my cleric on a horse and off (theoretically gaining him extra sit regen perhaps), and on the horse saves/gains him TONS of mana.<br>
<br>
Btw, since you have your epic I assume you realise you can epic/manarobe for ~ft28 outdoors? You cant do that without a horse.<br>
<br>
Also, you may be able to time sitting between draughts (despite the fact that that would annoy most people to do), but you cant with AT/SoS. And any time you want to chaincast nuke-concussion-nuke (which hopefully is at least sometimes else it's a darn boring group) you'll lose regen.<br>
<br>
As you progress you'll find yourself more and more limited by aggro rather than mana regen. The no sit-aggro from the horse allows you to nuke harder than otherwise for sure. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A> at: 6/5/03 6:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balicosdalinar>Balicos Dalinar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 6:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Urgent question on horses/drogmors, please help.</span><hr size=1> Has any of us ever gotten better at meditation while on a horse? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/napalm2/gumbum/balicos.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zupe>Zupe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>User Interface Prodigy</span><br>  Posts: 899<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 8:29 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Urgent question on horses/drogmors, please help.</span><hr size=1> Yes, my shaman had a horse and was getting meditation skill ups. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
